With some, we have made progress in the negotiations," said Paul Kaidl's group spokesman.
So maybe the future is promising.
According to informal information, it seems that we might be able to welcome the first virtual operator already at the end of the year.
But for the moment, his creation is accompanied by total silence.
"At this moment, we do not think there is any place on the Czech market for a virtual operator as such.
The Czech market is comparable to other very specific ones.
For the moment, no subject of a complex and serious project in this area has contacted us," Vlastimil Sršeň of the Telefonika O2 Press Department, in his statement for Mobil.cz.
Other operators also relate to the specificity of the Czech market.
The T-Mobile spokesman Martina Kemrová says in a rare agreement with the O2: "We have not registered for a viable and bilateral advantage project, which could serve as a basis."
She added: "It is practically excluded that a virtual operator appears in the T-Mobile network at the end of the year.
In order to operate in a limited period of time, we should now have a specific agreement."
Vodafone rather focuses on meeting requests to obtain its own 3G license.
Miroslav Čepický says in this regard: "We are open to negotiations with potential virtual operators, especially in the area of shared costs and infrastructures.
That's what we think means most of our customers' views.
Vodafone's main strategy in this area is the discovery of a partner to put in place a common network for a fast mobile Internet."
Responsible authorities: in phase with operators
The trend of mobile operators is easy to understand, the entry of another operator would mean an increase in competition, would have led to a lower price and therefore a lower benefit.
What, then, is to facilitate the development of such a competitor?
When it comes to their interests, operators know how to run in the field. The Chinese accompanying the creation of the U:phone also testifies.
The biggest pressure on the ČTú, when the U:fon was created, was exercised by T-Mobile company.
