In August 2008, domestic industrial sales prices increased by 0.1 per cent compared to the previous month, and 12.9 per cent compared to the month of August 2007 - the Central Statistics Office of Hungary reported.
Industrial export sales prices increased by 1.1 per cent compared to July 2008, while compared to the previous year, they decreased by 3.9 per cent.
As a result of fluctuations in domestic and export prices, industrial production prices increased by 0.7 per cent compared to those of the previous month and 3.2 per cent compared to those of the previous year.
Internal industrial sales prices have only increased to a minimum: 0.1 per cent compared to the previous month.
The domestic sales prices in the processing industry have only increased by 0.1 per cent from July to July.
In August 2008, the most significant price increase was observed in the leather and shoe manufacturing sector (2.8 per cent), with first place, the manufacture of bags and belts with a monthly increase of 4.6 per cent, then the production of shoes with 2.5 per cent monthly increase.
