A decline in oil processing (1.4 per cent) resulted in the production of machinery and electrical equipment (0.9 per cent), as well as a minimal increase in wood processing (0.1 per cent).
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing activities have not changed.
The other sectors of the transformation industry recorded an increase of 0.2 per cent and 0.9 per cent.
In the energy, gas, steam and water supply sectors, which represent an important weight in national industrial operation, prices increased by 0.3 per cent in August, mainly due to the impact of the increase in gas prices imposed by the authorities since 1 July.
In a 12-month comparison, taking into account the internal sales of transformation sectors, these are the prices of the oil processing sector which have known the most significant increase (32.4%).
In the manufacturing of metallurgy products, an increase in prices of 13.2 per cent was observed, while in the important area of food, drink and tobacco production, prices increased by 11 per cent.
Price reductions were made in textile and textile production sectors (2.5 per cent), as well as in the manufacture of electrical machinery and equipment (0.3 per cent).
In the other sectors of the transformation industry, prices increased from 0.6 per cent to 9.1 per cent.
In the entire transformation industry, prices increased by 10.2 per cent during the school year.
The prices of electricity, gas, steam and water supply sectors exceeded 18.7 per cent of the previous year.
Among the internal trade groups and according to sectoral allocation, in August, these are the investment-initiators sectors that have shown the most significant monthly price increase (0.7%).
In the consumer goods production sectors, prices increased by 0.3 per cent, while the energy and material production sectors for subsequent processing did not know about change over the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month of the previous year, the most important increase in energy and material production sectors was observed in subsequent transformation (16.8 per cent).
In the consumer goods production sectors, inflation was 6.8 per cent, while in the profit-producing sectors, a decrease of 1.4 per cent was observed.
The export prices of the industrial sector in HUF increased by 1.1 per cent in August compared to the previous month, while they fell by 3.9 per cent over 12 months.
